    <h1>Moft Z</h1>
    <h2>FOLD&#xAD;ABLE LAP&#xAD;TOP STAND</h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200902/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-02"><time>2020-09-02</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | TECH</span>
        - <span role="byline">Com&#xAD;piled by Trevor Tan</span>
    </section>

    <p>$89.90</p>
    <p>The Moft Z is no or­di­nary lap­top stand. With its origami-in­spired de­sign, it pro­vides four modes for sit­ting and one for stand­ing when perched on a desk.</p>
    <p>It can be tilted 25 or 35 de­grees when you are typ­ing on your lap­top, 45 de­grees for a work set-up with a mouse and ex­ter­nal key­board, and 60 de­grees when you are browsing the Web or watch­ing Net­flix on smaller de­vices such as tablets.</p>
    <p>It can also be turned into a 25.4cm­tall stand if you pre­fer to stand while work­ing.</p>

